cockle
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:any of a group of edible, bivalve molluscs with ribbed shells; in NZ applied chiefly to two shellfish of different genera: A. <i>Chione stutchburyi</i> tuangi; and less often B. <i>Amphidesma australe</i> pipi; in NZ often called pipi; littleneck clam
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
