Date: 0/0/1986
Source: NZ Fishes: An Identification Guide
Author: PAUL
Vol / Page: 158
Edition:
Quote: <i>Cockle Austrovenus stutchburyi </i>The so-called cockle of New Zealand, from its superficial similarity to the European cockle. However, the species is really a venus clam (faily Veneridae) being closely related to species of hardshell clam popular in North America.
Notes:

